thread.title_full: Australian market set to open lower

author: news.com.au
title: lower
text:
Thursday closed higher for a second session.
AAP Share Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google+ Share on Reddit Email a friend THE Australian stock market looks set to open lower following a weak lead from Wall Street.
At 0703 AEST on Friday, the December share price index futures contract was down 18 points at 5,063.
Wall Street stocks finished mostly flat as investors react to mixed US economic data and wait for Fridayâ€™s much anticipated US non farm payrolls employment report.
In local economic news on Friday, the Australian Bureau of Statistics releases August retail trade figures.
 Thursday closed higher for a second session in a row in the wake of positive overseas leads and better-than-expected Chinese manufacturing data.
